WorldStage Newsonline– Pharma-Deko Plc, which manufactures, packages and markets a range of pharmaceutical and consumer products in Nigeria has released the result of its operations for the year ended December 2020 with 5% decline in revenue to N461.753 million from N484.574 million  in 2019 The company was able to cut its by 13% to N241.378 million from N278.883 million loss in 2019.